THE MAGUS' REST SYSTEM

This trigger can be used to turn rest restrictions on or off.
Or to establish an area as sheltered and thus suitable for rest - which you can check for in the function ResterRequirements() in the rest_include script.

Adjust local variables on the trigger to chang settings
REST_UNRESTRICTED = 1
   will establish unrestricted rest for the player (this takes precedence over all other settings)
REST_RESTRICTED = 1
   will establish restricted rest for the player if area or module is set to unrestricted

Allow the PC to ignore a particular rest test while inside the trigger:
REST_IGNORE_TIME
REST_IGNORE_WARMTH
REST_IGNORE_BED
REST_IGNORE_FOOD

You may also define the text given to the PC when they enter or exit the trigger
These are local strings on the trigger
REST_MESSAGE_ENTER
REST_MESSAGE_EXIT

if the strings are empty no message will be given to the PC.

This is the default waypoint you may place to set a patrol path for a creature or NPC.
1. Create the creature and either use its current Tag or fill in a new one.
2. Place or make sure the WalkWayPoints() is within the body of the On Spawn script for the creature.
3. Place a series of waypoints along the route you wish the creature to walk.
4. Select all of the newly created waypoints and right click. Choose the Create Set option.
5. The waypoint set will have a set name of "WP_" + NPC Tag. Thus if an NPC with the Tag "Guard" will have a waypoint set called "WP_Guard". Note that Tags are case sensitive.

2. Place or make sure the WalkWayPoints() is within the body of the On Spawn script for the creature.
3. Place a series of waypoints along the route you wish the creature to walk.
4. Select all of the newly created waypoints and right click. Choose the Create Set option.
5. The waypoint set will have a set name of "WP_" + NPC Tag. Thus if an NPC with the Tag "Guard" will have a waypoint set called "WP_Guard". Note that Tags are case sensitive.
